column5: Where did the thread on the Lund with the 9.9 for sale go (by fisndevil)? I have checked the classifieds and can't find it. Jim
Sorry it was marked as SOLD in the early evening yesterday. Lots of good deals in the classifieds here and they go pretty quickly.

That was a great deal and the people I had turned onto it would have bid more than he was asking, and driven up there to pick it up today! I have forwarded the other 14'er with the 15 hp out of the classifieds. Hopefully it will suit their needs. Jim
It's been sold too, unless that was your friends....
Wow that's fast I wish I had a few boats for sale now. lol   Art

Yes my boat sold last night !!!! The first person to see it bought it !!!!! He drove from almost north bay down to buy it !!!!!! And I'm still getting calls on it I'm amazed their was that much interest in it  sounds like I could have got more it as guys were trying to buy it over the phone....

Always the case Shawn... ask too much it sits.. ask to little it's gone in a flash and you think to yourself "I should have asked for more". It's out of your hair.. money in your pocket.. good for you!
Sort of how it went with our house. It wasn't on the market 12 hours and we had a firm offer at 97% of our asking price.
